{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Ki|19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","chapter":19,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":1,"text":"When King Hezekiah heard their report, he tore his clothes, covered himself with sackcloth, and went into the Lord’s temple.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":2,"text":"He sent Eliakim, who was in charge of the palace, Shebna the court secretary, and the leading priests, who were covered with sackcloth, to the prophet Isaiah son of Amoz.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":3,"text":"They said to him, “This is what Hezekiah says: ‘Today is a day of distress, rebuke, and disgrace, for children have come to the point of birth, but there is no strength to deliver them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":4,"text":"Perhaps the Lord your God will hear all the words of the royal spokesman, whom his master the king of Assyria sent to mock the living God, and will rebuke him for the words that the Lord your God has heard. Therefore, offer a prayer for the surviving remnant.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":5,"text":"So the servants of King Hezekiah went to Isaiah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":6,"text":"who said to them, “Tell your master, ‘The Lord says this: Don’t be afraid because of the words you have heard, with which the king of Assyria’s attendants have blasphemed me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":7,"text":"I am about to put a spirit in him, and he will hear a rumor and return to his own land, where I will cause him to fall by the sword.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":8,"text":"When the royal spokesman heard that the king of Assyria had pulled out of Lachish, he left and found him fighting against Libnah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":9,"text":"The king had heard concerning King Tirhakah of Cush, “Look, he has set out to fight against you.” So he again sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":10,"text":"“Say this to King Hezekiah of Judah: ‘Don’t let your God, on whom you rely, deceive you by promising that Jerusalem will not be handed over to the king of Assyria.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":11,"text":"Look, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the countries: They completely destroyed them. Will you be rescued?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":12,"text":"Did the gods of the nations that my predecessors destroyed rescue them —nations such as Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the Edenites in Telassar?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":13,"text":"Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city of Sepharvaim, Hena, or Ivvah?’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":14,"text":"Hezekiah took the letter from the messengers’ hands, read it, then went up to the Lord’s temple, and spread it out before the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":15,"text":"Then Hezekiah prayed before the Lord:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":16,"text":"Listen closely, Lord, and hear; open your eyes, Lord, and see. Hear the words that Sennacherib has sent to mock the living God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":17,"text":"Lord, it is true that the kings of Assyria have devastated the nations and their lands.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":18,"text":"They have thrown their gods into the fire, for they were not gods but made by human hands —wood and stone. So they have destroyed them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":19,"text":"Now, Lord our God, please save us from his power so that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you, Lord, are God —you alone.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":20,"text":"Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent a message to Hezekiah: “The Lord, the God of Israel says, ‘I have heard your prayer to me about King Sennacherib of Assyria.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":21,"text":"This is the word the Lord has spoken against him: Virgin Daughter Zion despises you and scorns you; Daughter Jerusalem shakes her head behind your back.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":22,"text":"Who is it you mocked and blasphemed? Against whom have you raised your voice and lifted your eyes in pride? Against the Holy One of Israel!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":23,"text":"You have mocked the Lord through your messengers. You have said, ‘With my many chariots I have gone up to the heights of the mountains, to the far recesses of Lebanon. I cut down its tallest cedars, its choice cypress trees. I came to its farthest outpost, its densest forest.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":24,"text":"I dug wells and drank water in foreign lands. I dried up all the streams of Egypt with the soles of my feet.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":25,"text":"Have you not heard? I designed it long ago; I planned it in days gone by. I have now brought it to pass, and you have crushed fortified cities into piles of rubble.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":26,"text":"Their inhabitants have become powerless, dismayed, and ashamed. They are plants of the field, tender grass, grass on the rooftops, blasted by the east wind.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":27,"text":"But I know your sitting down, your going out and your coming in, and your raging against me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":28,"text":"Because your raging against me and your arrogance have reached my ears, I will put my hook in your nose and my bit in your mouth; I will make you go back the way you came.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":29,"text":"“This will be the sign for you: This year you will eat what grows on its own, and in the second year what grows from that. But in the third year sow and reap, plant vineyards and eat their fruit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":30,"text":"The surviving remnant of the house of Judah will again take root downward and bear fruit upward.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":31,"text":"For a remnant will go out from Jerusalem, and survivors, from Mount Zion. The zeal of the Lord of Armies will accomplish this.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":32,"text":"Therefore, this is what the Lord says about the king of Assyria: He will not enter this city, shoot an arrow here, come before it with a shield, or build up a siege ramp against it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":33,"text":"He will go back the way he came, and he will not enter this city.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":34,"text":"I will defend this city and rescue it for my sake and for the sake of my servant David.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":35,"text":"That night the angel of the Lord went out and struck down one hundred eighty-five thousand in the camp of the Assyrians. When the people got up the next morning —there were all the dead bodies!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":36,"text":"So King Sennacherib of Assyria broke camp and left. He returned home and lived in Nineveh.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","bookOrder":11,"chapter":19,"verse":37,"text":"One day, while he was worshiping in the temple of his god Nisroch, his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him down with the sword and escaped to the land of Ararat. Then his son Esar-haddon became king in his place.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Ki","chapter":19,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,8,14,16,20,22,23,24,25,26,27,28,29,32,33,34,35,37],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Hezekiah Seeks Isaiah’s Counsel"},{"beforeVerse":8,"text":"Sennacherib’s Departing Threat"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"Hezekiah’s Prayer"},{"beforeVerse":20,"text":"God’s Answer through Isaiah"},{"beforeVerse":35,"text":"Defeat and Death of Sennacherib"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":22,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":23,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":24,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":25,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":26,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":27,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":28,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":32,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":33,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":34,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When King Hezekiah heard their report, he tore his clothes, covered himself with sackcloth, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 21:27","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:37","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":37,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 69:11","book":"Psa","chapter":69,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and went into the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 32:20","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":20,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:1","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 21:27","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":27},{"label":"2Kg 18:37","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":37},{"label":"Ps 69:11","book":"Psa","chapter":69,"verse":11},{"label":"2Ch 32:20","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":20},{"label":"Is 37:1","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He sent Eliakim, who was in charge of the palace, Shebna the court secretary, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:26","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:37","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":37,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the leading priests, who were covered with sackcloth, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 3:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":31,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" to the prophet Isaiah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 1:1","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 2:1","book":"Isa","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" son of Amoz. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:26","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":26},{"label":"2Kg 18:37","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":37},{"label":"2Sm 3:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":31},{"label":"Is 1:1","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":1},{"label":"Is 2:1","book":"Isa","chapter":2,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They said to him, “This is what Hezekiah says: ‘Today is a day of distress, rebuke, and disgrace, for children have come to the point of birth, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Hs 13:13","book":"Hos","chapter":13,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" but there is no strength to deliver them. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Hs 13:13","book":"Hos","chapter":13,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Perhaps the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 17:26","book":"1Sa","chapter":17,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" will hear "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 14:12","book":"Jos","chapter":14,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 16:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":16,"verse":12,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" all the words of the royal spokesman, whom his master the king of Assyria sent to mock the living God, and will rebuke "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 50:21","book":"Psa","chapter":50,"verse":21,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" him for the words that the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God has heard. Therefore, offer a prayer for the surviving remnant.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:30","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":30,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 1:9","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":9,"letter":"g"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 17:26","book":"1Sa","chapter":17,"verse":26},{"label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35},{"label":"Jos 14:12","book":"Jos","chapter":14,"verse":12},{"label":"2Sm 16:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":16,"verse":12},{"label":"Ps 50:21","book":"Psa","chapter":50,"verse":21},{"label":"2Kg 19:30","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":30},{"label":"Is 1:9","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So the servants of King Hezekiah went to Isaiah, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"who said to them, “Tell your master, ‘The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says this: Don’t be afraid "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:6","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" because of the words you have heard, with which the king of Assyria’s attendants "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" have blasphemed "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:22","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":22,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:30","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":30,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" me. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 37:6","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":6},{"label":"2Kg 18:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":17},{"label":"2Kg 18:22","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":22},{"label":"2Kg 18:30","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":30},{"label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I am about to put a spirit in him, and he will hear a rumor and return to his own land, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 7:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":7,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" where I will cause him to fall by the sword.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":35,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 7:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":7,"verse":6},{"label":"2Kg 19:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":35}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:8–13","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" the royal spokesman heard that the king of Assyria had pulled out of Lachish, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:14","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" he left and found him fighting against Libnah. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 10:29","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":29,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 37:8–13","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":8},{"label":"2Kg 18:14","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":14},{"label":"Jos 10:29","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The king had heard concerning King Tirhakah of Cush, “Look, he has set out to fight against you.” So he again sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Say this to King Hezekiah of Judah: ‘Don’t let your God, on whom you rely, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" deceive you by promising that Jerusalem will not be handed over to the king of Assyria. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:29","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":29,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":5},{"label":"2Kg 18:29","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Look, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the countries: They completely destroyed them. Will you be rescued? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Did the gods of the nations "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:33","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":33,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" that my predecessors destroyed rescue them —nations such as Gozan, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Haran, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 11:31","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":31,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" Rezeph, and the Edenites "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:12","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":12,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" in Telassar? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:33","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":33},{"label":"2Kg 18:35","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":35},{"label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6},{"label":"Gn 11:31","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":31},{"label":"Is 37:12","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city of "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or king of Lair,"},{"kind":"text","text":" Sepharvaim, Hena, or Ivvah?’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:34","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":34,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:34","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":34}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or king of Lair,"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Hezekiah took "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:14–20","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" the letter "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 5:7","book":"2Ki","chapter":5,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" from the messengers’ hands, read it, then went up to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple, and spread it out before the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:14","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 37:14–20","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":14},{"label":"2Kg 5:7","book":"2Ki","chapter":5,"verse":7},{"label":"Is 37:14","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Hezekiah prayed before the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":":"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Listen closely, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", and hear; open your eyes, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", and see. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:28","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 115:4–6","book":"Psa","chapter":115,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 9:18","book":"Dan","chapter":9,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Hear the words that Sennacherib has sent to mock the living God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 31:2","book":"Psa","chapter":31,"verse":2,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:17","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":17,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 8:28","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":28},{"label":"Ps 115:4–6","book":"Psa","chapter":115,"verse":4},{"label":"Dn 9:18","book":"Dan","chapter":9,"verse":18},{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"Ps 31:2","book":"Psa","chapter":31,"verse":2},{"label":"Is 37:17","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is true that the kings of Assyria have devastated the nations and their lands. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:34","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":34,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:34","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":34}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They have thrown their gods into the fire, for they were not gods but made by human hands —wood and stone. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 44:9–20","book":"Isa","chapter":44,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 10:3–5","book":"Jer","chapter":10,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 17:29","book":"Act","chapter":17,"verse":29,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" So they have destroyed them. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 44:9–20","book":"Isa","chapter":44,"verse":9},{"label":"Jr 10:3–5","book":"Jer","chapter":10,"verse":3},{"label":"Ac 17:29","book":"Act","chapter":17,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" our God, please save us from his power so that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", are God —you alone. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:42","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":42,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 43:10–11","book":"Isa","chapter":43,"verse":10,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 8:42","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":42},{"label":"Is 43:10–11","book":"Isa","chapter":43,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:21–35","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Isaiah son of Amoz sent a message to Hezekiah: “The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", the God of Israel says, ‘I have heard your prayer "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 20:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" to me about King Sennacherib of Assyria.’ "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:21","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":21,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 37:21–35","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":21},{"label":"2Kg 20:5","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":5},{"label":"Is 37:21","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"This is the word the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has spoken against him:"},{"kind":"text","text":" Virgin Daughter Zion "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 14:17","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lm 2:13","book":"Lam","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" despises you and scorns you;"},{"kind":"text","text":" Daughter Jerusalem"},{"kind":"text","text":" shakes her head behind your back. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 22:7–8","book":"Psa","chapter":22,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 109:25","book":"Psa","chapter":109,"verse":25,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:39","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":39,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 14:17","book":"Jer","chapter":14,"verse":17},{"label":"Lm 2:13","book":"Lam","chapter":2,"verse":13},{"label":"Ps 22:7–8","book":"Psa","chapter":22,"verse":7},{"label":"Ps 109:25","book":"Psa","chapter":109,"verse":25},{"label":"Mt 27:39","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":39}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Who is it you mocked and blasphemed? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Against whom have you raised your voice"},{"kind":"text","text":" and lifted your eyes in pride?"},{"kind":"text","text":" Against the Holy One of Israel! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 5:24","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 30:11–15","book":"Isa","chapter":30,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 51:5","book":"Jer","chapter":51,"verse":5,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"2Kg 19:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":6},{"label":"Is 5:24","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":24},{"label":"Is 30:11–15","book":"Isa","chapter":30,"verse":11},{"label":"Jr 51:5","book":"Jer","chapter":51,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You have mocked the Lord "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Many mss read Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":" through "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit by the hand of"},{"kind":"text","text":" your messengers. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" You have said, ‘With my many chariots "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 20:7","book":"Psa","chapter":20,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 50:37","book":"Jer","chapter":50,"verse":37,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" I have gone up to the heights of the mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":" to the far recesses of Lebanon."},{"kind":"text","text":" I cut down its tallest cedars,"},{"kind":"text","text":" its choice cypress trees."},{"kind":"text","text":" I came to its farthest outpost,"},{"kind":"text","text":" its densest forest."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:17","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":17},{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"Ps 20:7","book":"Psa","chapter":20,"verse":7},{"label":"Jr 50:37","book":"Jer","chapter":50,"verse":37}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Many mss read Lord"},{"marker":2,"text":"Lit by the hand of"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I dug wells"},{"kind":"text","text":" and drank water in foreign lands."},{"kind":"text","text":" I dried up all the streams of Egypt "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 19:6","book":"Isa","chapter":19,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" with the soles of my feet.’"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 19:6","book":"Isa","chapter":19,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Have you not heard? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 40:21","book":"Isa","chapter":40,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 45:7","book":"Isa","chapter":45,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" I designed it long ago;"},{"kind":"text","text":" I planned it in days gone by."},{"kind":"text","text":" I have now brought it to pass, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 10:5","book":"Isa","chapter":10,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and you have crushed fortified cities"},{"kind":"text","text":" into piles of rubble."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 40:21","book":"Isa","chapter":40,"verse":21},{"label":"Is 45:7","book":"Isa","chapter":45,"verse":7},{"label":"Is 10:5","book":"Isa","chapter":10,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Their inhabitants have become powerless,"},{"kind":"text","text":" dismayed, and ashamed."},{"kind":"text","text":" They are plants of the field,"},{"kind":"text","text":" tender grass,"},{"kind":"text","text":" grass on the rooftops, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 129:6","book":"Psa","chapter":129,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" blasted by the east wind. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"DSS; MT reads blasted before standing grain; Is 37:27"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 129:6","book":"Psa","chapter":129,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"DSS; MT reads blasted before standing grain; Is 37:27"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But I know your sitting down, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 139:1–2","book":"Psa","chapter":139,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" your going out and your coming in,"},{"kind":"text","text":" and your raging against me."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 139:1–2","book":"Psa","chapter":139,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Because your raging against me"},{"kind":"text","text":" and your arrogance have reached my ears,"},{"kind":"text","text":" I will put my hook in your nose "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 19:9","book":"Ezk","chapter":19,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 29:4","book":"Ezk","chapter":29,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 38:4","book":"Ezk","chapter":38,"verse":4,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and my bit in your mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":" I will make you go back"},{"kind":"text","text":" the way you came."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezk 19:9","book":"Ezk","chapter":19,"verse":9},{"label":"Ezk 29:4","book":"Ezk","chapter":29,"verse":4},{"label":"Ezk 38:4","book":"Ezk","chapter":38,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“This will be the sign "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:14","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 20:8","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":8,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 7:14","book":"Isa","chapter":7,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" for you: This year you will eat what grows on its own, and in the second year what grows from that. But in the third year sow and reap, plant vineyards and eat their fruit. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 3:14","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":14},{"label":"2Kg 20:8","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":8},{"label":"Is 7:14","book":"Isa","chapter":7,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The surviving remnant "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 32:22–23","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":22,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the house of Judah will again take root downward and bear fruit upward. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"2Ch 32:22–23","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For a remnant will go out from Jerusalem, and survivors, from Mount Zion. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 10:20","book":"Isa","chapter":10,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" The zeal of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies will accomplish this. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 9:7","book":"Isa","chapter":9,"verse":7,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 10:20","book":"Isa","chapter":10,"verse":20},{"label":"Is 9:7","book":"Isa","chapter":9,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:32","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Therefore, this is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says about the king of Assyria:"},{"kind":"text","text":" He will not enter this city,"},{"kind":"text","text":" shoot an arrow here,"},{"kind":"text","text":" come before it with a shield,"},{"kind":"text","text":" or build up a siege ramp against it. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 8:7–10","book":"Isa","chapter":8,"verse":7,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 8:7–10","book":"Isa","chapter":8,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:33","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He will go back"},{"kind":"text","text":" the way he came,"},{"kind":"text","text":" and he will not enter this city."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:34","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will defend this city and rescue it"},{"kind":"text","text":" for my sake and for the sake of my servant David.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 20:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 31:5","book":"Isa","chapter":31,"verse":5,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 11:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":12},{"label":"2Kg 20:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":20,"verse":6},{"label":"Is 31:5","book":"Isa","chapter":31,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:35","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"That night the angel of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" went out and struck down one hundred eighty-five thousand in the camp of the Assyrians. When the people got up the next morning —there were all the dead bodies! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 32:21","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:36","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":36,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Ch 32:21","book":"2Ch","chapter":32,"verse":21},{"label":"Is 37:36","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":36}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:36","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So King Sennacherib of Assyria broke camp and left. He returned home and lived in Nineveh. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jnh 1:2","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":2,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jnh 1:2","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Ki:19:37","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"One day, while he was worshiping in the temple of his god Nisroch, his sons Adrammelech "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:31","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Sharezer struck him down with the sword and escaped to the land of Ararat. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 8:4","book":"Gen","chapter":8,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 51:27","book":"Jer","chapter":51,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Then his son Esar-haddon "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 10:11","book":"Gen","chapter":10,"verse":11,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 4:2","book":"Ezr","chapter":4,"verse":2,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" became king in his place."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 17:31","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":31},{"label":"Gn 8:4","book":"Gen","chapter":8,"verse":4},{"label":"Jr 51:27","book":"Jer","chapter":51,"verse":27},{"label":"Gn 10:11","book":"Gen","chapter":10,"verse":11},{"label":"Ezr 4:2","book":"Ezr","chapter":4,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279423320}